'''Wammu''' is a computer program that can manage contacts, calendar schedules or messages on a cellphone via a [[graphical user interface]]. It uses [[Gammu (software)|Gammu]] software libraryand works with cellphones from Nokia, Sony-Ericsson, Motorola, Samsung and Siemens.<ref>[http://wammu.eu/phones/ Database of supported phones]</ref>
==History== The Wammu project was started in 2003 to create a universal application to manage [[mobile phones]] under Linux. Since 2003 it has evolved quite a lot, but there are still lot of rough areas and places to improve. Current project leader is Michal ÄihaÅ.<ref>http://wammu.eu/authors/</ref>
==Features== * Supports sending [[SMS]] (with delivery report), picture messages, can send/receive ring tones (as SMS) * [[Phonebook]] * Dial/Receive calls * Calendar * Todo list * Notes
==See also== * [[OpenSync]] - Open Source synchronization framework * [[Gammu (software)|Gammu]] - a program for communicating with [[mobile phone]]s * [[Gnokii]] - a program for communicating with [[mobile phone]]s * [[BitPim]] - Open Source CDMA management and synchronization software * [[Series60-Remote]] - GUI program for S60 phones
